---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Services — Hobbes Digital"
  description="Strategy, execution, and measurement — three things, done well, by the same small team."
>

  <!-- Page hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">What we do</span>
      <h1>Practical marketing, run by people, measured against revenue.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        We don't offer a menu of services. We offer a relationship. You get
        a small team that thinks about your business the way you do — and
        does the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services list -->
  <section class="services-page-list">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="service-row">
        <span class="service-row-number">01</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Strategy</h3>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>
            Before we do anything, we build a plan. A real one — written
            down, with a hypothesis for why it will work and a clear measure
            of when it hasn't. No slide decks full of frameworks. A plain
            document you can hand to anyone in your business and have them
            understand in 20 minutes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Strategy includes an audit of what you're currently doing,
            competitive landscape research, and a 90-day playbook with
            weekly priorities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-row">
        <span class="service-row-number">02</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Execution</h3>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>
            We do the work ourselves. Content, paid ads, local SEO, email,
            partnerships, listing management — whatever the plan calls for.
            We don't outsource to junior freelancers and mark it up.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most of our clients are in F&B, retail, healthcare, or
            professional services. We know the constraints: tight margins,
            small teams, owners who wear five hats. We work around that.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-row">
        <span class="service-row-number">03</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Measurement</h3>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>
            Every month, a written report. Plain English. Revenue and
            footfall first, then the metrics that lead to them. We tell you
            what worked, what didn't, and what we're changing.
          </p>
          <p>
            We don't hide behind impressions and reach numbers when the
            restaurant is still half-empty on Tuesdays. The report is a
            conversation, not a defense.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Process -->
  <section class="process-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-divider">
        <span class="eyebrow">How we work</span>
      </div>
      <h2 style="max-width:640px; margin-bottom:0;">
        The first 90 days. Then we re-earn it.
      </h2>
      <div class="process-steps">
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-num">01</div>
          <h4>The conversation</h4>
          <p>30 minutes. You tell us about the business; we tell you what we'd do. No pitch deck. A written note follows either way.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-num">02</div>
          <h4>The plan</h4>
          <p>If we're a fit, we spend two weeks writing a 90-day strategy. You approve it before we touch anything.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-num">03</div>
          <h4>The work</h4>
          <p>Execution starts. Weekly check-ins, a shared task board, no surprises. You're always in the loop without being in the weeds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-num">04</div>
          <h4>The review</h4>
          <p>At 90 days we review against the plan. If the results aren't there, we say so. We either fix the plan or part ways — your call.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quote -->
  <section class="quote-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="quote-inner">
        <blockquote>
          "We'd been burned before by agencies that promised the world
          and delivered reports. Hobbes just&hellip; did the work."
        </blockquote>
        <div class="quote-attribution">
          <div class="quote-avatar">S</div>
          <div>
            <div class="quote-meta-name">Siti Rahimah</div>
            <div class="quote-meta-role">Owner, Rahimah Bridal, Geylang</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Ready when you are</p>
      <h2>
        Tell us about your business.<br />
        <em>We'll tell you what we'd do.</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        No pressure, no pitch deck. A 30-minute conversation, and a written
        note from us afterwards either way.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Start a conversation →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
